Here''s the plain version of what it means: you''ve got the same CSS property written twice in some places — once the standard way, once the old browser-specific way. Tailwind sees both and gets confused, drops one, and Chrome users end up with no blur effect on the live site even though it looks fine when you''re testing locally.

The fix is simple — just delete the redundant hand-written version everywhere it appears and let Tailwind handle it automatically.

