The key property you''re describing is that it **won''t pop** — meaning it has enough structural integrity to push through holes repeatedly without rupturing. That''s actually important for the design because the inner ball needs to be able to protrude AND retract cleanly.

That material paired with a flexible rubber outer sleeve — the two materials working together is what makes the mechanic work.

Here''s what I''m curious about now — when you imagine this as a finished product on a shelf, who is it for? You mentioned your kid and yourself both reacted. Are you thinking children''s toy, adult stress/fidget tool, or something that bridges both?', '0f57989c-27e1-4ecd-8832-b094efc869f2', '2026-06-13T00:24:38.210Z', 'message', NULL, NULL, FALSE, FALSE) ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;

