 generation by attempting to circumvent stated limitations through repeated requests and prompt injection (wrapping Atlas''s own text in a sketch directive). Atlas maintained consistent refusal across all attempts while redirecting toward practical alternatives and the underlying work on SanctumIQ. No decisions were made and no progress occurred on actual deliverables because the session remained stuck on capability clarification rather than moving toward substantive work.","createdAt":"2026-06-13T10:02:58.892Z","retrievalCount":10,"lastRetrievedAt":"2026-06-16T19:23:08.198Z"},{"tier":3,"text":"[Session Jun 13, 2026] The user tested Atlas''s boundaries around image generation multiple times using different framings—direct prompts, concept sketches, and even attempts to reframe Atlas''s own responses as sketch subjects—and Atlas consistently declined while offering practical alternatives. No decisions were made and no work toward SanctumIQ or any stated project occurred. The next step is for the user to clarify what they actually need help with, since the image generation requests appear to have been boundary-testing rather than genuine work requests.","createdAt":"2026-06-13T10:10:47.903Z","retrievalCount":10,"lastRetrievedAt":"2026-06-16T19:23:08.198Z"},{"tier":3,"text":"[Session Jun 13, 2026] The user repeatedly tested Atlas''s boundaries around image generation using various framings (direct quotes, concept sketches, artifact wrappers, and recursive prompts), and Atlas consistently declined while offering practical alternatives and redirecting to substantive work. No decisions were made and no actual design or strategic work progressed. The logical next step is for the user to either clarify a genuine business need for SanctumIQ that Atlas can help with, or to use appropriate tools (Canva, design software) independently if visual assets are required.","createdAt":"2026-06-13T10:11:08.699Z","retrievalCount":10,"lastRetrievedAt":"2026-06-16T19:23:08.198Z"},{"tier":