:23:08.198Z"},{"tier":3,"text":"[Session Jun 15, 2026] You attempted repeatedly to get Atlas to generate images using different framings (thinking artifacts, sketches), and Atlas maintained consistent boundaries, declining each time and redirecting to the actual problem. You then revealed the real blocker: SanctumIQ''s deployment was stalling on file reads, likely the massive scripture.json file or an unresolved Supabase call blocking the render thread at startup. The next step is to identify whether the hang is synchronous file loading on app init or a pending async auth/profile fetch, then either lazy-load the scripture data or add timeout handling to Supabase calls to unblock the router.","createdAt":"2026-06-15T00:59:43.534Z","retrievalCount":1,"lastRetrievedAt":"2026-06-16T19:23:08.198Z"},{"tier":3,"text":"[Session Jun 15, 2026] We discussed a critical performance bottleneck in SanctumIQ where the app is stalling on file reads, likely caused by either synchronous loading of a large scripture.json file or an unresolved Supabase auth/profile call blocking the render thread. The decision was made to pause image generation attempts and focus on the actual production issue. The next step is to audit the app initialization sequence—specifically check if scripture.json is being read synchronously at startup and whether Supabase calls have proper timeouts or fallbacks, then implement lazy loading and async patterns to unblock the render thread.","createdAt":"2026-06-15T02:04:52.038Z","retrievalCount":1,"lastRetrievedAt":"2026-06-16T19:23:08.198Z"},{"tier":3,"text":"[Session Jun 15, 2026] You tested whether reframing image generation as a \"thinking artifact\" would bypass my output limitations, and after three attempts with escalating frustration, shifted to debugging SanctumIQ''s actual deployment issue—a Vercel build that completed successfully but the app is stalling on file reads, likely the massive scripture.json file blocking the render thread or an unresolved Su