together into a cohesive web product. The next step is for you to articulate the actual vision and purpose for this Axiom project so we can move from exploratory UI tweaks into strategic planning and intentional building.","createdAt":"2026-06-11T09:57:30.752Z","retrievalCount":3,"lastRetrievedAt":"2026-06-12T00:52:13.029Z"},{"tier":3,"text":"[Session Jun 11, 2026] The user requested a simple dark HTML page with a gold \"Axiom\" title, then asked Atlas to add a subtle pulsing animation to it, which was completed. The user then asked about Atlas''s capabilities for building tangible outputs like images, blueprints, and websites, and Atlas clarified it could handle all of those through different tools depending on the project needs. The user inquired what project they were working on, Atlas noted it appeared to be called \"Friendly Greeting Assistant\" but acknowledged the work so far had been exploratory rather than goal-directed, and asked for clarification on the actual vision for Axiom. The next step is for the user to define what Axiom actually is—whether it''s a brand identity, product, tool, or something else—so that strategic building can begin rather than continue in exploratory mode.","createdAt":"2026-06-11T19:11:48.647Z","retrievalCount":2,"lastRetrievedAt":"2026-06-12T00:52:13.029Z"},{"tier":3,"text":"[Session Jun 12, 2026] The user explored what Atlas could deliver across different mediums—starting with a plain HTML page with dark background and gold pulsing \"Axiom\" title, then testing the boundaries of image generation, attempting photorealistic renders and mood boards only to discover Atlas cannot generate actual image files but can create code-based visuals and provide strategic direction instead. The key decision was clarifying Atlas''s actual capabilities: code, HTML, SVG diagrams, and text blueprints yes; photorealistic renders and curated mood boards no, though Atlas can guide the creative direction and provide prompts for external tools. The logical next step was to refocus on what Axiom actually is—whether it''s a brand, product, or tool—so that future sessions could move from capability testing into concrete building with a clear vision.","createdAt":"2026-06-12T00:52:43.545Z","retrievalCount":0,"lastRetrievedAt":null}]}', NULL, NULL, NULL, '{"goal":{"x":300,"y":250,"type":"goal","label":"Ship Friendly Greeting Assistant","details":"What does shipping Friendly Greeting Assistant actually look like? Tap to sharpen the outcome.","resolved":false},"guest-list":{"x":160,"y":140,"type":"requirement","label":"Guest list","moscow":"must","details":"A roster of knowledgeable guests — locals, travelers, urban writers — lined up per city.","question":"Which cities and guest types do you lead with to set the tone for the whole show?","resolved":false},"record-pilot":{"x":300,"y":390,"type":"sprint","label":"Record pilot episode","moscow":"must","details":"Produce a single pilot episode to validate format, length, and guest chemistry before committing to weekly cadence.","question":"Which city does the pilot spotlight, and why would that hook a first-time listener?","resolved":false},"episode-length":{"x":440,"y":140,"type":"decision","label":"Episode length","moscow":"must","details":"Still undecided how long each episode should run — short-form (20 min) vs long-form (60 min+).","question":"Does the underrated-cities format reward deep storytelling or punchy highlights?","resolved":false},"recording-gear":{"x":170,"y":360,"type":"blocker","label":"Recording equipment","moscow":"must","details":"No microphone, interface, or recording setup yet — nothing can be recorded until this is resolved.","question":"What is the minimum viable gear to record a guest remotely and still sound credible?","resolved":false},"solo-vs-cohost":{"x":460,"y":310,"type":"decision","label":"Solo vs. co-host format","moscow":"must","details":"Open choice between hosting alone or bringing on a permanent co-host for each episode.","question":"Would a co-host add a consistent voice of curiosity, or dilute the guest-focused city spotlight?","resolved":false},"release-cadence":{"x":390,"y":410,"type":"requirement","label":"Release cadence","moscow":"should","details":"A defined weekly publishing schedule and episode pipeline to stay consistently ahead of release.","question":"How many episodes do you want banked before you go public?","resolved":false},"weekly-city-podcast":{"x":300,"y":250,"type":"goal","label":"Weekly underrated cities show","moscow":"must","details":"Publish a weekly podcast shining a light on underrated cities around the world.","question":"What does success look like after the first 10 episodes — audience size, guest caliber, or something else?","resolved":false},"flow-1780696455062-0":{"x":160,"y":140,"type":"blocker","label":"No recording equipment","question":"What''s the minimum viable setup to record your first episode — USB mic + free DAW, or something more?","resolved":false},"flow-1780696455062-1":{"x":360,"y":140,"type":"decision","label":"Solo vs. co-host","question":"Do you want a consistent co-host from episode one, or start solo and let the format evolve?","resolved":false},"flow-1780696455062-2":{"x":560,"y":140,"type":"requirement","label":"Guest sourcing system","question":"How will you find and vet guests — local journalists, city tourism boards, travel writers, Reddit communities?","resolved":false}}', '[]', NULL, NULL, '2026-06-02T15:10:30.692Z', '2026-06-12T00:52:43.546Z', 'project', '2026-06-02T15:10:30.692Z', NULL, 'operational', '{"v":1}', NULL, '2026-06-02T15:10:30.684Z') ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
